### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@tenant1 = 1
@tenant2 = 2

### ========================================
### HEALTH CHECK
### ========================================

### Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### ========================================
### USERS - CRUD BÁSICO
### ========================================

### 1. Crear usuario en Tenant 1
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant1}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstname": "Juan",
  "lastname": "Pérez",
  "dni": "12345678",
  "gender": "M",
  "phone": "+573001234567",
  "email": "juan@example.com",
  "birth_day": "1990-01-15T00:00:00Z"
}

### 2. Crear usuario en Tenant 1 (Manager)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant1}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstname": "María",
  "lastname": "González",
  "dni": "87654321",
  "gender": "F",
  "phone": "+573007654321",
  "email": "maria@example.com",
  "birth_day": "1992-05-20T00:00:00Z"
}

### 3. Crear usuario en Tenant 1 (User básico)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant2}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstname": "Carlos",
  "lastname": "Rodríguez",
  "dni": "1122334455",
  "gender": "M",
  "phone": "+573009887654",
  "email": "carlost2@example.com",
  "birth_day": "1988-12-10T00:00:00Z"
}

### 4. Listar usuarios de Tenant 1
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant2}}

### 5. Obtener usuario por ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/1
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant1}}

### 6. Buscar por DNI
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/search?dni=12345678
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant1}}

### 7. Actualizar usuario
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/1
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant1}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "juan.updated@example.com",
  "phone": "+573001111111"
}

### 8. Eliminar usuario (soft delete)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/3
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant1}}

### ========================================
### TESTING MULTI-TENANCY
### ========================================

### 20. Crear usuario con mismo DNI en Tenant 2 (debe funcionar)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant2}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstname": "Pedro",
  "lastname": "Tenant2",
  "dni": "12345678",
  "gender": "M",
  "phone": "+573002222222",
  "email": "pedro@tenant2.com",
  "birth_day": "1991-02-02T00:00:00Z"
}

### 21. Listar usuarios de Tenant 2 (no debe ver usuarios de Tenant 1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant2}}

### 22. Intentar acceder a usuario de Tenant 1 desde Tenant 2 (debe fallar)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users/1
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant2}}

### ========================================
### CASOS DE ERROR
### ========================================

### 23. Sin X-Tenant-ID (debe dar error 400)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users

### 24. DNI duplicado en mismo tenant (debe dar error 409)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant1}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstname": "Duplicado",
  "lastname": "Test",
  "dni": "12345678",
  "gender": "M",
  "phone": "+573003333333",
  "email": "duplicado@example.com",
  "birth_day": "1990-01-01T00:00:00Z"
}

### 25. Email inválido (debe dar error 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant1}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstname": "Test",
  "lastname": "Invalid",
  "dni": "88888888",
  "gender": "M",
  "phone": "+573008888888",
  "email": "email-sin-arroba",
  "birth_day": "1990-01-01T00:00:00Z"
}

### 26. Usuario menor de edad (debe dar error 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant1}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstname": "Test",
  "lastname": "Menor",
  "dni": "77777777",
  "gender": "M",
  "phone": "+573007777777",
  "email": "menor@example.com",
  "birth_day": "2010-01-01T00:00:00Z"
}

### 27. Género inválido (debe dar error 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant1}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstname": "Test",
  "lastname": "Genero",
  "dni": "66666666",
  "gender": "X",
  "phone": "+573006666666",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "birth_day": "1990-01-01T00:00:00Z"
}

### ========================================
### ROLES - CRUD
### ========================================

### 9. Listar roles disponibles (creados por SQL)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/roles
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant1}}

### 10. Obtener rol por ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/roles/1
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant1}}

### 11. Crear rol personalizado
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/roles
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant1}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "ventas",
  "description": "Equipo de ventas"
}

### 12. Actualizar rol
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/roles/1
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant1}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Equipo de ventas y marketing",
  "is_active": true
}

### 13. Eliminar rol personalizado (NO roles del sistema)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/roles/4
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant1}}

### ========================================
### ASIGNACIÓN DE ROLES A USUARIOS
### ========================================

### 14. Asignar rol "admin" a Juan (user_id=1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/roles/assign
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant1}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": 1,
  "role_id": 1
}

### 18. Asignar permiso a rol personalizado (action_id=1 = users.create)
# Primero necesitas saber el action_id de la BD
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/roles/1/permissions
X-Tenant-ID: {{tenant1}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action_id": 1
}
